nz.co.jedsimson.lgp.core.program.registers

Class Arguments<TData>

  • nz.co.jedsimson.lgp.core.program.registers.Arguments<TData>
  • Type Parameters:
    TData -

    The type of the arguments.


    public class Arguments<TData>

    A simple collection of class Arguments.

    The sole purpose of this wrapper class is to make the syntax of functions for operations a bit cleaner. For example, we can write:

    // A simple cosine function definition
val cos: (Arguments) -> Double = { args -> Math.cos(args.get(0)) }

    Instead of:

    // A verbose cosine function definition
val cos: (List>) -> Double = { args -> Math.cos(args.get(0)) }

    See Also:
    class Argument
